#Categorizing 3 groups based on Number of Groups
solos = df[df['numGroups']>50]
duos = df[(df['numGroups']>25) & (df['numGroups']<=50)]
squads = df[df['numGroups']<=25]
f,ax1 = plt.subplots(figsize =(20,10))

#XGBOOST MODEL Implementation
import xgboost as xgb
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split
from sklearn.preprocessing import Normalizer

df.dropna(subset=['winPlacePerc'], inplace=True)

X=df.drop(["Id","groupId","matchId","matchType","winPlacePerc"], axis=1)
Y=df['winPlacePerc']

col_names=X.columns
transformer=Normalizer().fit(X)
X=transformer.transform(X)
In [4]:
X=pd.DataFrame(X,columns=col_names)

D_train=xgb.DMatrix(X_train,label=Y_train)
D_test=xgb.DMatrix(X_test,label=Y_test)
